'''羅伯·丹屯''' （Robert Darnton，{{bd|1939年|5月10日}}）是美國著名的歷史家，學術專長是十八世紀的法國文化史。

==簡介==
丹屯畢業於美國[[哈佛大學|哈佛大學]]，並於1960年進入[[牛津大學|牛津大學]]攻讀博士學位。

==著作==
*''Mesmerism and the End of the Enlightenment in France'' (1968), [[Harvard_University_Press|Harvard University Press]]
*''The Business of Enlightenment: A Publishing History of the Encyclopédie, 1775-1800'' (1979), Harvard University Press
*''The Literary Underground of the Old Regime'' (1982), Harvard University Press 
*《貓大屠殺：法國文化史鉤沉》
*''Revolution in Print: the Press in France 1775-1800'' (1989) edited with [[Daniel_Roche|Daniel Roche]]
*''The Kiss of Lamourette: Reflections in Cultural History'' (1989)
*''Edition et sédition. L'univers de la littérature clandestine au XVIIIe siècle'' (1991) 
*''Berlin Journal, 1989-1990'' (1991) 
*''Gens de lettres, gens du livre'' (1992)
*{{cite book|title=The Forbidden Best-Sellers of Prerevolutionary France|year=1995|isbn=0-393-31442-1|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=EqkybhL_t2IC&printsec=frontcover&dq=The+Forbidden+Best-Sellers+of+Prerevolutionary+France&source=bl&ots=BS6pLWqdQJ&sig=LbxM86PhHd9SAGJENqc_vGQ0Rkg&hl=en&ei=W04JTaHNH4O0lQfmv9ynAg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CCIQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=The%20Forbidden%20Best-Sellers%20of%20Prerevolutionary%20France&f=false}}
*''The Corpus of Clandestine Literature in France, 1769-1789'' (1995)
*''George Washington's False Teeth: An Unconventional Guide to the Eighteenth Century'' (June 2004)
*''The Case for Books: Past, Present, and Future'' (October 2009)
*''The Devil in the Holy Water, or the Art of Slander from Louis XIV to Napoleon'' (December 2009)

